<h2>Press</h2>

<p>We're honored to have been mentioned across the web:</p>

<ul>
<li>February 2012: <a href="http://www.women2.org/the-power-of-cooperative-outreach-diversifying-pycon/">Diversifying PyCon: the power of cooperative outreach</a>, the story of the Boston Python Workshop and other outreach events working together to get a woman named Pam attending PyCon for the first time, at Women 2.0</li>
<li>December 2011: <a href="http://trishofalltrades.tumblr.com/post/14496033030/boston-python-workshop-for-n00bs">Boston Python Workshop for n00bs</a>, a write-up on the 5th Boston Python Workshop by attendee Trish Fontanilla</li>
<li>November 2011: <a href="http://pyfound.blogspot.com/2011/11/boston-python-workshop-psf-grant.html">Boston Python Workshop PSF Grant</a> at Python Software Foundation News</li>
<li>October 2011: <a href="http://blogs.gnome.org/marina/2011/10/08/my-ada-lovelace-day-heroines/">My Ada Lovelace Day Heroines</a> at Marina'z Blog, <a href="http://geekfeminism.org/2012/01/18/wednesday-geek-women-joanmarie-diggs-mairin-duffy-jessica-mckellar-stormy-peters/">reblogged on Geek Feminism</a></li>
<li>July 2011: <a href="http://geekfeminism.org/2011/07/02/lessons-learned-from-the-boston-python-workshop-an-outreach-event-for-women/">Lessons learned from the Boston Python Workshop, an outreach event for women</a> on Geek Feminism</li>
<li>June 2011: <a href="http://www.women2.org/roundup-python-outreach-workshops-for-women/">Roundup: Python Outreach Workshops for Women</a> at Women 2.0</li>
</ul>

<h2>How the event has spread</h2>

<p>Since we <a href="http://python.mirocommunity.org/video/4259/pycon-2011-get-new-contributor">spoke about the effort at PyCon 2011</a>, people around the world have started efforts inspired by ours. We've:</p>

<ul>
<li>September 2011: Traveled to Philadelphia to help teach at <a href="http://www.thehacktory.org/?p=1470">PyStar Philadelphia</a></li>
<li>July 2011: Traveled to Scalathon to organize a <a href="http://workshops.railsbridge.org/2011/06/scala-outreach-workshop/">Scala Crash Course for women and their friends</a></li>
<li>May 2011: Worked with Montreal Python to organize an <a href="http://montrealpython.org/2011/05/a-success-introduction-to-python-for-women/">Introduction to Python for Women</a></li>
<li>April 2011: Inspired the global <a href="http://pyladies.com/">PyLadies</a> effort and collaborated on talk proposals</li>
<li>March 2011: Inspired <a href="http://pystar.org/">PyStar</a> to form and organize outreach events</li>
</ul>

<h2>Help us tell our story</h2>

<p>If you write about technology or diversity, we would love for you to share our story. Read about the event's <a href="about/">results</a>, and <a href="https://openhatch.org/contact/">drop us a line</a>!</p>

<p>You are free to use <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/paulproteus/sets/">photos from past events</a> under the Creative Commons license on each photo.</p>

EOD;

